The paper discusses distributed computing frameworks and proposes a new model using stateless functions. This topic falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed model using Python, which falls under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for stateless functions to be used in future computing environments, which falls under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
